12/* The following token may be returned by XmlContentTok */
13#define XML_TOK_TRAILING_RSQB -5 /* ] or ]] at the end of the scan; might be
14 start of illegal ]]> sequence */
15/* The following tokens may be returned by both XmlPrologTok and
16 XmlContentTok.
17*/
18#define XML_TOK_NONE -4 /* The string to be scanned is empty */
19#define XML_TOK_TRAILING_CR -3 /* A CR at the end of the scan;
20 might be part of CRLF sequence */
21#define XML_TOK_PARTIAL_CHAR -2 /* only part of a multibyte sequence */
22#define XML_TOK_PARTIAL -1 /* only part of a token */
23#define XML_TOK_INVALID 0
24
25/* The following tokens are returned by XmlContentTok; some are also
26 returned by XmlAttributeValueTok, XmlEntityTok, XmlCdataSectionTok.
27*/
28#define XML_TOK_START_TAG_WITH_ATTS 1
29#define XML_TOK_START_TAG_NO_ATTS 2
30#define XML_TOK_EMPTY_ELEMENT_WITH_ATTS 3 /* empty element tag <e/> */
31#define XML_TOK_EMPTY_ELEMENT_NO_ATTS 4
32#define XML_TOK_END_TAG 5
33#define XML_TOK_DATA_CHARS 6
34#define XML_TOK_DATA_NEWLINE 7
35#define XML_TOK_CDATA_SECT_OPEN 8
36#define XML_TOK_ENTITY_REF 9
37#define XML_TOK_CHAR_REF 10 /* numeric character reference */
38
39/* The following tokens may be returned by both XmlPrologTok and
40 XmlContentTok.
41*/
42#define XML_TOK_PI 11 /* processing instruction */
43#define XML_TOK_XML_DECL 12 /* XML decl or text decl */
44#define XML_TOK_COMMENT 13
45#define XML_TOK_BOM 14 /* Byte order mark */
46
47/* The following tokens are returned only by XmlPrologTok */
48#define XML_TOK_PROLOG_S 15
49#define XML_TOK_DECL_OPEN 16 /* <!foo */
50#define XML_TOK_DECL_CLOSE 17 /* > */
51#define XML_TOK_NAME 18
52#define XML_TOK_NMTOKEN 19
53#define XML_TOK_POUND_NAME 20 /* #name */
54#define XML_TOK_OR 21 /* | */
55#define XML_TOK_PERCENT 22
56#define XML_TOK_OPEN_PAREN 23
57#define XML_TOK_CLOSE_PAREN 24
58#define XML_TOK_OPEN_BRACKET 25
59#define XML_TOK_CLOSE_BRACKET 26
60#define XML_TOK_LITERAL 27
61#define XML_TOK_PARAM_ENTITY_REF 28
62#define XML_TOK_INSTANCE_START 29
63
64/* The following occur only in element type declarations */
65#define XML_TOK_NAME_QUESTION 30 /* name? */
66#define XML_TOK_NAME_ASTERISK 31 /* name* */
67#define XML_TOK_NAME_PLUS 32 /* name+ */
68#define XML_TOK_COND_SECT_OPEN 33 /* <![ */
69#define XML_TOK_COND_SECT_CLOSE 34 /* ]]> */
70#define XML_TOK_CLOSE_PAREN_QUESTION 35 /* )? */
71#define XML_TOK_CLOSE_PAREN_ASTERISK 36 /* )* */
72#define XML_TOK_CLOSE_PAREN_PLUS 37 /* )+ */
73#define XML_TOK_COMMA 38
74
75/* The following token is returned only by XmlAttributeValueTok */
76#define XML_TOK_ATTRIBUTE_VALUE_S 39
77
78/* The following token is returned only by XmlCdataSectionTok */
79#define XML_TOK_CDATA_SECT_CLOSE 40
80
81/* With namespace processing this is returned by XmlPrologTok for a
82 name with a colon.
83*/
84#define XML_TOK_PREFIXED_NAME 41

93#define XML_N_STATES 3
94#endif /* not XML_DTD */

96#define XML_PROLOG_STATE 0
97#define XML_CONTENT_STATE 1
98#define XML_CDATA_SECTION_STATE 2
99#ifdef XML_DTD
100#define XML_IGNORE_SECTION_STATE 3
101#endif /* XML_DTD */

103#define XML_N_LITERAL_TYPES 2
104#define XML_ATTRIBUTE_VALUE_LITERAL 0
105#define XML_ENTITY_VALUE_LITERAL 1

107/* The size of the buffer passed to XmlUtf8Encode must be at least this. */

128typedef int (PTRCALL *SCANNER)(const ENCODING *,
129 const char *,
130 const char *,
131 const char **);

133enum XML_Convert_Result {
134 XML_CONVERT_COMPLETED = 0,
135 XML_CONVERT_INPUT_INCOMPLETE = 1,
136 XML_CONVERT_OUTPUT_EXHAUSTED = 2 /* and therefore potentially input remaining as well */
137};

139struct encoding {
140 SCANNER scanners[XML_N_STATES];
141 SCANNER literalScanners[XML_N_LITERAL_TYPES];
142 int (PTRCALL *sameName)(const ENCODING *,
143 const char *,
144 const char *);
145 int (PTRCALL *nameMatchesAscii)(const ENCODING *,
146 const char *,
147 const char *,
148 const char *);
149 int (PTRFASTCALL *nameLength)(const ENCODING *, const char *);
150 const char *(PTRFASTCALL *skipS)(const ENCODING *, const char *);
151 int (PTRCALL *getAtts)(const ENCODING *enc,
152 const char *ptr,
153 int attsMax,
154 ATTRIBUTE *atts);
155 int (PTRFASTCALL *charRefNumber)(const ENCODING *enc, const char *ptr);
156 int (PTRCALL *predefinedEntityName)(const ENCODING *,
157 const char *,
158 const char *);
159 void (PTRCALL *updatePosition)(const ENCODING *,
160 const char *ptr,
161 const char *end,
162 POSITION *);
163 int (PTRCALL *isPublicId)(const ENCODING *enc,
164 const char *ptr,
165 const char *end,
166 const char **badPtr);
167 enum XML_Convert_Result (PTRCALL *utf8Convert)(const ENCODING *enc,
168 const char **fromP,
169 const char *fromLim,
170 char **toP,
171 const char *toLim);
172 enum XML_Convert_Result (PTRCALL *utf16Convert)(const ENCODING *enc,
173 const char **fromP,
174 const char *fromLim,
175 unsigned short **toP,
176 const unsigned short *toLim);
177 int minBytesPerChar;
178 char isUtf8;
179 char isUtf16;
180};

182/* Scan the string starting at ptr until the end of the next complete
183 token, but do not scan past eptr. Return an integer giving the
184 type of token.
185
186 Return XML_TOK_NONE when ptr == eptr; nextTokPtr will not be set.
187
188 Return XML_TOK_PARTIAL when the string does not contain a complete
189 token; nextTokPtr will not be set.
190
191 Return XML_TOK_INVALID when the string does not start a valid
192 token; nextTokPtr will be set to point to the character which made
193 the token invalid.
194
195 Otherwise the string starts with a valid token; nextTokPtr will be
196 set to point to the character following the end of that token.
197
198 Each data character counts as a single token, but adjacent data
199 characters may be returned together. Similarly for characters in
200 the prolog outside literals, comments and processing instructions.
201*/
202
203
204#define XmlTok(enc, state, ptr, end, nextTokPtr) \
205 (((enc)->scanners[state])(enc, ptr, end, nextTokPtr))
206
207#define XmlPrologTok(enc, ptr, end, nextTokPtr) \
208 XmlTok(enc, XML_PROLOG_STATE, ptr, end, nextTokPtr)
209
210#define XmlContentTok(enc, ptr, end, nextTokPtr) \
211 XmlTok(enc, XML_CONTENT_STATE, ptr, end, nextTokPtr)
212
213#define XmlCdataSectionTok(enc, ptr, end, nextTokPtr) \
214 XmlTok(enc, XML_CDATA_SECTION_STATE, ptr, end, nextTokPtr)
215
216#ifdef XML_DTD
217
218#define XmlIgnoreSectionTok(enc, ptr, end, nextTokPtr) \
219 XmlTok(enc, XML_IGNORE_SECTION_STATE, ptr, end, nextTokPtr)
220
221#endif /* XML_DTD */
222
223/* This is used for performing a 2nd-level tokenization on the content
224 of a literal that has already been returned by XmlTok.
225*/
226#define XmlLiteralTok(enc, literalType, ptr, end, nextTokPtr) \
227 (((enc)->literalScanners[literalType])(enc, ptr, end, nextTokPtr))
228
229#define XmlAttributeValueTok(enc, ptr, end, nextTokPtr) \
230 XmlLiteralTok(enc, XML_ATTRIBUTE_VALUE_LITERAL, ptr, end, nextTokPtr)
231
232#define XmlEntityValueTok(enc, ptr, end, nextTokPtr) \
233 XmlLiteralTok(enc, XML_ENTITY_VALUE_LITERAL, ptr, end, nextTokPtr)
234
235#define XmlSameName(enc, ptr1, ptr2) (((enc)->sameName)(enc, ptr1, ptr2))
236
237#define XmlNameMatchesAscii(enc, ptr1, end1, ptr2) \
238 (((enc)->nameMatchesAscii)(enc, ptr1, end1, ptr2))
239
240#define XmlNameLength(enc, ptr) \
241 (((enc)->nameLength)(enc, ptr))
242
243#define XmlSkipS(enc, ptr) \
244 (((enc)->skipS)(enc, ptr))
245
246#define XmlGetAttributes(enc, ptr, attsMax, atts) \
247 (((enc)->getAtts)(enc, ptr, attsMax, atts))
248
249#define XmlCharRefNumber(enc, ptr) \
250 (((enc)->charRefNumber)(enc, ptr))
251
252#define XmlPredefinedEntityName(enc, ptr, end) \
253 (((enc)->predefinedEntityName)(enc, ptr, end))
254
255#define XmlUpdatePosition(enc, ptr, end, pos) \
256 (((enc)->updatePosition)(enc, ptr, end, pos))
257
258#define XmlIsPublicId(enc, ptr, end, badPtr) \
259 (((enc)->isPublicId)(enc, ptr, end, badPtr))
260
261#define XmlUtf8Convert(enc, fromP, fromLim, toP, toLim) \
262 (((enc)->utf8Convert)(enc, fromP, fromLim, toP, toLim))
263
264#define XmlUtf16Convert(enc, fromP, fromLim, toP, toLim) \
265 (((enc)->utf16Convert)(enc, fromP, fromLim, toP, toLim))
